        "jsCode": "// Loop over input items and add a new field called 'myNewField' to the JSON of each one\nfor (const item of $input.all()) {\n  const dateOffset = (24*60*60) / 2; // half a day\n  const date = new Date((parseInt(item.json.timestamp) + dateOffset) * 1000).toISOString().split('T')[0];\n  const now = new Date(Date.now()).toISOString().split('T')[0]\n  \n  item.json.date = date;\n  item.json.isToday = date == now;\n}\n\nreturn $input.all();"
      },
